sweet /swiːt/

(sweeter,sweets,sweetest) 

1. ADJ Sweet food and drink contains a lot of sugar. 甜的 

例： ...a mug of sweet tea. …一杯甜茶。 

例： If the sauce seems too sweet, add a dash of red wine vinegar. 如果酱太甜，就加少许红酒醋。 

2. sweetness N-UNCOUNT 甜味 

例： Florida oranges have a natural sweetness. 佛罗里达柑桔有一种天然的甜味。 

3. ADJ A sweet smell is a pleasant one, for example the smell of a flower. 芳香的 

例： ...the sweet smell of her shampoo. …她的洗发水芳香的味道。 

4. ADJ A sweet sound is pleasant, smooth, and gentle. 悦耳的 

例： Her voice was as soft and sweet as a young girl's. 她的声音和小女孩的一样温柔悦耳。 

5. sweetly ADV 悦耳地 

例： He sang much more sweetly than he has before. 他唱歌比以前悦耳多了。 

6. ADJ If you describe something as sweet , you mean that it gives you great pleasure and satisfaction. 令人痛快的 [书面] 

例： There are few things quite as sweet as revenge. 几乎没有什么事情像复仇一样让人痛快。 

7. ADJ If you describe someone as sweet , you mean that they are pleasant, kind, and gentle toward other people. 温柔的 

例： He was a sweet man but when he drank he tended to quarrel. 他是个温柔的男人，但一喝酒他就爱吵架。 

8. sweetly ADV 温柔地 

例： I just smiled sweetly and said no. 我只是温和地笑了笑，说了声“不”。 

9. ADJ If you describe a small person or thing as sweet , you mean that they are attractive in a simple or unsophisticated way. (小孩或小东西) 可爱的 [非正式] 

例： ...a sweet little baby girl. …一个可爱的小女婴。 

10. N-PLURAL Sweets are foods that have a lot of sugar. 甜食 [美国英语] 

例： To maintain her weight, she simply chooses fruits and vegetables over fats and sweets. 为了保持自己的体重，她选择只吃水果和蔬菜而不吃肥肉和甜食。 

11. N-COUNT Sweets are small sweet things such as chocolates and mints. 糖果 [英国英语] 

